Package org.neo4j.io

Enum ByteUnit

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<ByteUnit>
      • org.neo4j.io.ByteUnit
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<ByteUnit>
    public enum ByteUnit
extends Enum<ByteUnit>
    A ByteUnit is a unit for a quantity of bytes.

    The unit knows how to convert between other units in its class, so you for instance can turn a number of KiBs into an accurate quantity of bytes. Precision can be lost when converting smaller units into larger units, because of integer division.

    These units all follow the EIC (International Electrotechnical Commission) standard, which uses a multiplier of 1.024. This system is also known as the binary system, and has been accepted as part of the International System of Quantities. It is therefor the recommended choice when communicating quantities of information, and the only one available in this implementation.

      • factorFromPower

        private static long factorFromPower​(long power)
        Compute the increment factor from the given power.

        Giving zero always produces 1. Giving 1 will produce 1024, and so on.

      • bytesToStringWithoutScientificNotation

        public static String bytesToStringWithoutScientificNotation​(long bytes)
        The parse method doesn't support values with scientific notation. This bytes to string method builds a String representation that always uses decimal floating-point. This should be used when the String representation might get parsed e.g values used in documentation.
